        {
          "id": "1bbaac45-ae76-4db7-b85e-966a443ff13f",
          "date": "Aug 7-9",
          "title": "Suricata Safaris — 3-Day Group Camping Safari",
          "body": "Safari with Suricata Safaris Ltd. Day 1: Tarangire National Park (Twiga Camp Site, FB). Day 2: Lake Manyara National Park (Twiga Camp Site, FB). Day 3: Ngorongoro Crater (overnight at Jevas Hotel, HB). Safari package: $1,200 total for 2 pax. $240 deposit (20%) paid. $960 balance due on arrival in cash (post-2009 USD notes) or online via Pesapal (+5% surcharge): payments.pesapal.com/suricatasafaris. Contact: Richard, +255 763 222 293, info@suricatasafaris.com.",
          "category": "journal",
          "location": "Tarangire → Lake Manyara → Ngorongoro Crater, Tanzania",
          "contacts": "Richard (Suricata Safaris): +255 763 222 293, info@suricatasafaris.com",
          "origin": "tanzaniamemories.md"
        },
        {
          "id": "9790321e-5e85-45ca-b64e-8989cb934013",
          "date": "Aug 9",
          "title": "Ngorongoro Crater Day — One of the Best Days of the Trip",
          "body": "Driver guide: Emmanuel (not Richard) — excellent, pointed out wildlife before it was visible. Bought 2 beaded bracelets from a Maasai lady at the crater rim for Athina Mari — ~$20-25 USD / ~TZS 35,000, exact amount uncertain. Emmanuel mentioned an extra ranger tip at the gate: ~TZS 5,000 cash, separate from park fees — nobody told us beforehand. Described as one of the best days of the trip. Park fees for the day: entry permit $70.80/person, crater service fee $70.80/person, vehicle descent fee $295 (up to 2000kg). Ngorongoro nights are cold — warm layers needed.",
          "category": "journal",
          "location": "Ngorongoro Crater, Tanzania",
          "contacts": "Emmanuel (driver guide)",
          "origin": "voice memo transcription"
        },
